Jacob AUER v. Raymond James NITKEY et al. No. 8465. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Nov. 16, 1939. Kieran P. O’Gallagher, of Chicago, Ill., for appellant. George E. Alcorn, of Dayton, Ohio, for appellees.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ARANT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the motion of the Guardian Securities Company and the S. T. McKnight Company for leave to file motion to dismiss herein be and the same is granted.

It is further ordered that said motion to dismiss appeal be and the same is granted and the appeal is hereby dismissed.
